The government will fight tooth and claw to rein in hatemongers, ICT Permanent Secretary Sammy Itemere has said.He said responsible agencies will boldly tackle the threat, which risks plunging the country into violence.Itemere said leaders should avoid hate speech and instead strive towards national cohesion.He said politicians are fond of making unnecessary remarks towards elections.Itemere said organs such as the National Cohesion and Integration Commission will determine which remarks amount to hate speech.